Final (Dec 5-12)
Tigre             Arg   São Paulo               Bra     0-0x 0-2  0-2y
  [Lucas 22, Osvaldo 28]
x 1st leg at Boca Juniors.
y 2nd leg was abandoned after 45 minutes by the referee, as the Tigre players refused to come back to play the rest of the match after incidents at halftime.
  Therefore, São Paulo were declared as the champion.
 
 
First leg, Alberto J. Armando, Buenos Aires, att: 29.000,
         ref: Antonio Arias (PAR)
Tigre: Damián Albil; Norberto Paparatto, Mariano Echeverría, Alejandro Donatti, Lucas Orban;
  Diego Ferreira, Martín Galmarini, Gastón Díaz, Ramiro Leone; Rubén Botta, Ezequiel Maggiolo (Diego Ftacla 77.
  Coach: Nestor Gorosito.
São Paulo: Rogério Ceni; Rhodolfo, Paulo Miranda, Rafael Toloi, Bruno Cortes;
  Lucas Moura, Wellington, Denilson, Jadson (Cícero Santos 60), Osvaldo; Luis Fabiano. 
  Coach: Ney Franco.
Yellow Cards: Botta, Paparatto (T); Rafael Toloi, Rhodolfo, Denilson (SP).
Red Cards: Donatti (T); Luis Fabiano (SP) 
 
 
Second leg, Morumbí, San Pablo, att: 72.800,
          ref: Enrique Osses (CHI)
São Paulo: Rogério Ceni; Rhodolfo, Paulo Miranda, Rafael Toloi, Bruno Cortes;
  Lucas Moura, Wellington, Denilson, Jadson, Osvaldo (Douglas 45); Willian José. 
  Coach: Ney Franco.
Tigre: Damián Albil; Erik Godoy, Norberto Paparatto, Mariano Echeverría, Lucas Orban;
  Diego Ferreira, Martín Galmarini, Gastón Díaz, Ramiro Leone; Rubén Botta, Ezequiel Maggiolo (Diego Ftacla 77.
  Coach: Nestor Gorosito.
Yellow Cards: Denilson, Rogério Ceni, Osvaldo (SP); Galmarini, Godoy, G.Díaz.
Red Card: Paulo Miranda (SP) 45.
 
 
São Paulo champion Copa Sudamericana 2012.
 
 
